   First Gov site Rural Health Research In Progress in the Rural Health
   Research Centers Program March 2001 Book provides summary information
   about all the Rural Health Services research projects currently being
   conducted by the eight centers funded by the Office of Rural Health
   Policy.
   The 50 State Offices of Rural Health Learn about the State Offices of
   Rural Health (SORH) grant program, the Office of Rural Health Policy
   which administers the SORH, the National Organization of State Offices
   of Rural Health which represents those state offices and the Rural
   Hospital Flex Program which facilitates designation of Critical Access
   Hospitals.
   Selected Federal Programs: Meeting the Health Care Needs of Rural
   Americans This publication of the Capital Area Rural Health Roundtable
   describes Federal programs and federally-supported initiatives that
   support rural health care services. These programs and initiatives
   demonstrate how rural underserved areas rebuild their health care
   systems by building consortia, forming recruitment networks, and
   through other innovative methods. Contact information is provided for
   all programs described in this publication.


   The Proximity of Rural African American and Hispanic/Latino Communities
   to Physicians and Hospital Services
   Working paper presents results of a study to determine how local
   physician concentrations and distances to hospitals differ in rural
   communities with varying population levels of African Americans and
   Hispanics. Includes survey methods, results, and discussion. Concludes
   that rural minorities often must travel longer distances to obtain
   health services than do non-minority individuals.

